    dc:date "2011" ;
    dc:title "First record of the genus Disholcaspis Dalla Torre & Kieffer (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini) in the Neotropics, with description of two new species from Panama" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.277049>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.277050>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.277053>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.277054> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.277049>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Disholcaspis bettyannae: (A) Head anterior view. (B) Head posterior view. (C) Female antenna. (D) Detail of last flagellomeres. (E) Pronotum antero-dorsal view. (D) Mesosoma lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/277049/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.277050>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Disholcaspis bettyannae: (A) Mesosoma dorsal view. (B) Propodeum. (C) Metatarsal claw. (D) Metasoma lateral view. (E) Detail of ventral spine of hypopygium, lateral view. (F) Detail of ventral spine of hypopygium." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/277050/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.277053>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Habitus and forewings of Disholcaspis species: (A) Disholcaspis bettyannae, female (B) forewing of female. (C) Disholcaspis bisethiae, female. (D) forewing of female." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/277053/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.277054>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Galls of Disholcaspis species from Panama: (A) Immature gall of Disholcaspis bettyannae. (B) mature galls of Disholcaspis bettyannae. (C) Section of a gall showing the central cell. (D) Old gall of Disholcaspis bisethiae showing the exit holes of inducer. (E) Mature gall of Disholcaspis bisethiae. (F) Section of a gall showing the central cell." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/277054/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

